title: NRL grand final: Cheerleaders struggle to cover cost of getting to Sydney |
text:
Cowboys cheerleaders have to pay their own way to the grand final but they wouldn't miss it. Georgia Barnes, Eleanor White and Renee Nicol. PICTURE: FIONA HARDING Source: News Corp Australia
Former Cairns girl Georgia Evans is one of 12 Cowboys Spirit cheerleaders heading to Sydney on Sunday for the NRL Grand Final.
But with the inflated prices of airfares and accom­modation, she, along with the rest of the squad, is banking on some community support to help ease the burden.
While the Cowboys club has offered some support, the girls are hoping to raise another $6000 through an online crowd-funding website.
By late yesterday, the site had already accrued more than $500.
“We would appreciate any cent towards this opportunity ... to dance and support the Cowboys ... it’d just be an opportunity of a lifetime to be there with them.”
The Broncos cheer squad will be sending 10 of their best dancers to Sydney to perform at the Grand Final.
The group will take a mini-van from Brisbane to Sydney, thanks to sponsorship they have secured.
